    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's more than just \"possible\" though. it's like... i can actually feel it when they do it. like there is a specific frequency or a way they position themselves that just clicks in my head. it's almost like i can understand the intent behind the patterns. yesterday when the sparrows were doing that rapid fluttering near the oak tree, i knew instantly it wasn't just a storm coming, but a temperature drop that was gonna be way more sudden than the forecast said. it's like i'm tuned into a channel they're all broadcasting on. do you think there's a biological reason why some people might be able to pick up on these specific signals better than others?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
